## Real Example

Suppose Slack has 1 million users.

They cannot use just one WebSocket server.

So they use many servers:

```text
WS Server 1
WS Server 2
WS Server 3
WS Server 4
```

When a user connects:

* Load balancer sends them to one server
* That server stores their active socket

If another user wants to send them a message:

* Backend checks which server has that user
* Message is routed there

