# Why HTTP is Easier

HTTP is usually **stateless**.

Every request is independent:

```text
Request comes in
Server responds
Done
```

Any server can handle it.

But WebSocket connections stay alive for hours, so:

* server memory matters
* sticky routing matters
* connection tracking matters

