Use Apache Cassandra because chat systems mostly keep adding new messages, and users usually read messages in time order.

Append-heavy writes

Meaning:

new data keeps getting appended
old messages rarely change

Chat apps are mostly:

continuous inserts
sequential reads

conversation_id:  Groups all messages together.
message_timestamp: Inside that conversation, messages are sorted by time

| Concept             | Meaning                           |
| ------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Append-heavy writes | Mostly adding new messages        |
| Time-ordered reads  | Read chats chronologically        |
| conversation_id     | Groups messages by chat           |
| message_timestamp   | Sorts messages by time            |
| Composite key       | Combination for efficient storage |
| Cassandra           | Distributed high-write NoSQL DB   |


